						<summary>

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1471, Saumya, Pushya, śu. 9</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1549 December 28, Saturday</hi> (not verifiable). It refers itself to the reign of <hi rend="bold">Sadāśivadēva-Mahārāya</hi> and records that the king made a gift. of 4 <hi rend="italic">paḍis</hi> of rice per day out of the provision made for the service of god Anantaśayanadēva, for offerings to the god Hanumantadēva on the <hi rend="bold">Jambukēśvara</hi> hill.</p>						

						<p>First Face.</p>						

						</summary>
